<paragraph id="787EE036C338FFBCFF29D250FC6405D1" blockId="5.[136,1452,158,581]" pageId="5" pageNumber="218">
<emphasis id="4AB53C24C338FFBCFF29D250FEC30599" bold="true" box="[189,265,374,400]" pageId="5" pageNumber="218">Notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="BFC19BB5C338FFBCFEB2D251FE330599" authorityName="Srisanga &amp; Watthana" authorityYear="2021" box="[294,505,374,400]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Capparaceae" genus="Maerua" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="5" pageNumber="218" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="koratensis">
<emphasis id="4AB53C24C338FFBCFEB2D251FE330599" box="[294,505,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="218">Maerua koratensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="BFC19BB5C338FFBCFD1AD251FC6A0599" authority="subsp. juncea" box="[654,928,374,400]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Capparaceae" genus="Maerua" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="5" pageNumber="218" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="juncea" subSpecies="juncea">
<emphasis id="4AB53C24C338FFBCFD1AD251FD350599" box="[654,767,375,400]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="218">M. juncea</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="4AB53C24C338FFBCFCC1D251FC6A0599" box="[853,928,375,400]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="218">juncea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having petaliferous flowers with distinct 4- lobed laciniate disc and a similar number of stamens (
<bibRefCitation id="1C509DC7C338FFBCFD7AD2BCFC4A05BD" author="Killick, D. J. B." box="[750,896,410,436]" pageId="5" pageNumber="218" pagination="39 - 42" refId="ref3477" refString="Killick, D. J. B. (1969) The disc in the Southern African species of Maerua. Bothalia 10: 39 - 42. https: // doi. org / 10.4102 / abc. v 10 i 1.1507" type="journal article" year="1969">Killick 1969</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="1C509DC7C338FFBCFC1FD2BCFB9C05BD" author="Abreu, J. A. &amp; Martins, E. S. &amp; Catarino, L." box="[907,1110,410,436]" pageId="5" pageNumber="218" pagination="19 - 25" refId="ref2686" refString="Abreu, J. A., Martins, E. S. &amp; Catarino, L. (2014) New species of Maerua (Capparaceae) from Angola. Blumea 59: 19 - 25. https: // doi. org / 10.3767 / 000651914 X 681964" type="journal article" year="2014">
Abreu 
<emphasis id="4AB53C24C338FFBCFC4DD2BDFBD905BD" box="[985,1043,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="218">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="1C509DC7C338FFBCFBF6D2BCFAE905BD" author="Hyde, M. A. &amp; Wursten, B. T. &amp; Ballings, P. &amp; Coates Palgrave, M." box="[1122,1315,410,436]" pageId="5" pageNumber="218" refId="ref3153" refString="Hyde, M. A., Wursten, B. T., Ballings, P. &amp; Coates Palgrave, M. (2019) Flora of Zimbabwe: Species information: Maerua juncea subsp. juncea. Available from: https: // www. zimbabweflora. co. zw / speciesdata / species. php? species _ id = 124630 (accessed 6 June 2019)" type="url" year="2019">
Hyde 
<emphasis id="4AB53C24C338FFBCFB33D2BDFB2A05BD" box="[1191,1248,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="218">et al.</emphasis>
2019
</bibRefCitation>
, PROTA4U 2019), but can be distinguished as outlined in the diagnosis and 
<tableCitation id="3543D58DC338FFBCFCC1D298FC6205D1" box="[853,936,446,472]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="2.[136,224,556,580]" captionText="TABLE 1. Comparison of morphological characters between Maerua koratensis and M. juncea subsp. juncea." pageId="5" pageNumber="218">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="787EE036C338FFBCFF29D2C5FC0C064D" blockId="5.[136,1452,158,581]" pageId="5" pageNumber="218">
<taxonomicName id="BFC19BB5C338FFBCFF29D2C5FE4505F5" authorityName="Srisanga &amp; Watthana" authorityYear="2021" box="[189,399,482,508]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Capparaceae" genus="Maerua" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="5" pageNumber="218" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="koratensis">
<emphasis id="4AB53C24C338FFBCFF29D2C5FE4505F5" box="[189,399,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="218">Maerua koratensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only known from a restricted locality in 
<collectingRegion id="BA052ED4C338FFBCFCFDD2C4FB7C05F5" box="[873,1206,482,508]" country="Thailand" name="Nakhon Ratchasima" pageId="5" pageNumber="218">Nakhon Ratchasima Province</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="00D6A0A6C338FFBCFB54D2C4FAEC05F5" box="[1216,1318,482,508]" name="Thailand" pageId="5" pageNumber="218">Thailand</collectingCountry>
, South-East Asia whereas 
<taxonomicName id="BFC19BB5C338FFBCFEB7D121FDE40629" authority="subsp. juncea" box="[291,558,518,544]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Capparaceae" genus="Maerua" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="5" pageNumber="218" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="juncea" subSpecies="juncea">
<emphasis id="4AB53C24C338FFBCFEB7D121FE580629" box="[291,402,519,544]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="218">M. juncea</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="4AB53C24C338FFBCFE77D121FDE40629" box="[483,558,519,544]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="218">juncea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is confined to tropical East Africa: 
<collectingCountry id="00D6A0A6C338FFBCFC20D120FBD60629" box="[948,1052,518,544]" name="Tanzania" pageId="5" pageNumber="218">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="00D6A0A6C338FFBCFBB1D120FBB70629" box="[1061,1149,518,544]" name="Malawi" pageId="5" pageNumber="218">Malawi</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="00D6A0A6C338FFBCFB13D120FAD40629" box="[1159,1310,518,544]" name="Mozambique" pageId="5" pageNumber="218">Mozambique</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="00D6A0A6C338FFBCFABCD120FAB40629" box="[1320,1406,518,544]" name="Zambia" pageId="5" pageNumber="218">Zambia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="00D6A0A6C338FFBCFF1CD10CFEC9064D" box="[136,259,554,580]" name="Zimbabwe" pageId="5" pageNumber="218">Zimbabwe</collectingCountry>
, and tropical 
<collectingCountry id="00D6A0A6C338FFBCFE0ED10CFDE7064D" box="[410,557,554,580]" name="South Africa" pageId="5" pageNumber="218">South Africa</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingCountry id="00D6A0A6C338FFBCFDA3D10DFD62064C" box="[567,680,555,581]" name="Botswana" pageId="5" pageNumber="218">Botswana</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="00D6A0A6C338FFBCFD27D10CFCD9064D" box="[691,787,554,580]" name="Namibia" pageId="5" pageNumber="218">Namibia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="00D6A0A6C338FFBCFCDED10CFC08064D" box="[842,962,554,580]" name="Swaziland" pageId="5" pageNumber="218">Swaziland</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
